                    {
                        "unit_id": 3415,
                        "title": "Customer Segment",
                        "slug": "customer-segment",
                        "order": 10,
                        "status": "publish",
                        "content": "",
                        "media": {
                            "youtube_video_id": "_OKmGVLzZcg",
                            "banner_image_url": null,
                            "featured_image_url": null,
                            "pdf_template_url": null
                        },
                        "meta": {
                            "course-unit-read": "<h3 data-fontsize=\"24\" data-lineheight=\"26\">Where are our most important customers?</h3>\r\nCustomers are the livelihood of every company and successful organizations understand their customers and recognize how to derive value for them. They know how to reach them and they are aware of how, and what types of relationships to build with them. Most importantly, from the enterprise perspective, successful companies know how to turn satisfied customers into revenue streams.",
                            "course-unit-read-more": "<h3 data-fontsize=\"24\" data-lineheight=\"26\">Key questions to answer:</h3>\r\n<ol>\r\n \t<li> For whom are you creating value?</li>\r\n \t<li> Who are your most important customers and how do you define them?</li>\r\n \t<li> Can you group your customer in to segments based on common characteristics?</li>\r\n \t<li>How do you describe the market you wish to operate in, for example is it a:</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ul>\r\n \t<li> Niche marke</li>\r\n \t<li> Mass market</li>\r\n \t<li> Segmented</li>\r\n \t<li> Diversified</li>\r\n \t<li>Multi-sided platform</li>\r\n</ul>",
                            "course-unit-quotes": "",
