                    {
                        "unit_id": 3419,
                        "title": "Channels",
                        "slug": "channels",
                        "order": 30,
                        "status": "publish",
                        "content": "",
                        "media": {
                            "youtube_video_id": "p-0ko3tB3Zs",
                            "banner_image_url": null,
                            "featured_image_url": null,
                            "pdf_template_url": null
                        },
                        "meta": {
                            "course-unit-read": "<h3 data-fontsize=\"24\" data-lineheight=\"26\">How do we reach each of our client segments?</h3>\r\nA company reaches its customers through various communication and distribution channels. They represent the interface between a company, its value propositions and its customers. These customer touch points include advertising, retail outlets, sales teams, websites, conferences, sales affiliates and many more. The means a company can use to reach its customers have multiplied over the years. This has left managers with a large set of design choices to reach their customers.",
                            "course-unit-read-more": "<h3 data-fontsize=\"24\" data-lineheight=\"26\">Key questions to answer:</h3>\r\n<ol>\r\n \t<li> Through which communication and distribution channels do we reach our markets?</li>\r\n \t<li>How well does each channel work?</li>\r\n \t<li>How expensive or cost efficient is each of our channels?</li>\r\n \t<li>Through which communication and distribution channels do we promote and deliver each value proposition?</li>\r\n \t<li> Through which channels do we reach each customer segment?</li>\r\n</ol>",
                            "course-unit-quotes": "",
                            "course-unit-case-study": "",
